.TH "BSON_READER_NEW_FROM_FILE" "3" "2016\(hy03\(hy16" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_reader_new_from_file() \- Creates a new bson_reader_t using the file denoted by filename.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
bson_reader_t *
bson_reader_new_from_file (const char   *path,
                           bson_error_t *error);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B
.B path
A filename in the host filename encoding.
.LP
.TP
.B
.B error
A
.B bson_error_t
\e&.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Creates a new
.B bson_reader_t
using the file denoted by
.B filename
\e&.

.SH "ERRORS"

Errors are propagated via the
.B error
parameter.

.SH "RETURNS"

A newly allocated
.B bson_reader_t
on success, otherwise NULL and error is set.


.B
